OL,3,CEye and ear checks to be offered to
OL,4,Cthousands of children in special
OL,5,Cschools
OL,7,F"Having specialist services which take
OL,8,Faccount of an individual's reasonable
OL,9,Fadjustments, with support from people
OL,10,Fthat know them well and delivered by
OL,11,Fappropriately-trained staff, will help
OL,12,Fensure that they are able to access
OL,13,Fsensory checks that other children and
OL,14,Fyoung people routinely receive."
OL,16,FEyesight checks will be carried out
OL,17,Fannually, and at least one face-to-
OL,18,Fface annual dental check will be
OL,19,Foffered as a minimum, with health
OL,20,Fadvice and prevention visits also on
OL,21,Foffer.
